class Solution {
    public int[] numsSameConsecDiff(int n, int k) {
        List<Integer> res = new ArrayList<>();
        for (int d = 1; d <= 9; ++d) dfs(n - 1, k, d, res);
        return res.stream().mapToInt(i -> i).toArray();
    }
    private void dfs(int rem, int k, int cur, List<Integer> res) {
        if (rem == 0) { res.add(cur); return; }
        int last = cur % 10;
        if (last + k <= 9) dfs(rem - 1, k, cur * 10 + (last + k), res);
        if (k != 0 && last - k >= 0) dfs(rem - 1, k, cur * 10 + (last - k), res);
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(2^n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Depth-first search builds each valid number digit by digit, pruning branches early. Each step appends one digit differing by k from the last, avoiding leading zeros by starting digits 1-9. Output size is up to 2^n numbers, so the DFS is asymptotically optimal.

